  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A correct preoxygenation can be obtained after a 3min delay of calm ventilation through a
      tight mask thereafter mask is used to make the patient breathing before intubation. Most
      tight masks are actually sold but they have never been compared in studies. The aim of this
      study is to compare air leaks with standard facial mask and QuadraLite masks during
      preoxygenation and induction of anesthesia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
